\subsection{Newform subspace}
\begin{definition}\label{cmf.newform_subspace}
\uses{cmf.hecke_operator,cmf.level,cmf.newform,cmf.newspace}
The **newform subspace** of a {{KNOWL('cmf.newform', 'newform')}} $f$ in $S_k^{\rm new}(N,\chi)$ is the subspace generated by $T_p(f)$ for all {{KNOWL('cmf.hecke_operator', 'Hecke operators')}} $T_p$ for $p$ coprime to the {{KNOWL('cmf.level', 'level')}}, equivalently, the subspace generated by the Galois conjugates of $f$.

Every {{KNOWL('cmf.newspace', 'newspace')}} has a canonical decomposition into newform subspaces.
\end{definition}


